com.amazonaws.services.lambda.runtime

Interface Context


  • public interface Context
    The context object allows you to access useful information available within the Lambda execution environment

    • Method Summary

    • Method Detail

      • getAwsRequestId

        String getAwsRequestId()
        Gets the AWS request ID associated with the request.

        This is the same ID returned to the client that called invoke(). This ID is reused for retries on the same request.

      • getLogGroupName

        String getLogGroupName()
        Gets the CloudWatch log group that this container is configured to log to. The return value may be null:
        • If the container is not configured to log to CloudWatch.
        • If the role provided to the function does not have sufficient permissions.

      • getLogStreamName

        String getLogStreamName()
        Gets the CloudWatch log stream that this container is configured to log to. The return value may be null:
        • If the container is not configured to log to CloudWatch.
        • If the role provided to the function does not have sufficient permissions.

      • getFunctionName

        String getFunctionName()
        Gets the name of the function being executed.

      • getIdentity

        CognitoIdentity getIdentity()
        Gets information about the Amazon Cognito identity provider when invoked through the AWS Mobile SDK. It can be null

      • getClientContext

        ClientContext getClientContext()
        Gets information about the client application and device when invoked through the AWS Mobile SDK. It can be null.

      • getRemainingTimeInMillis

        int getRemainingTimeInMillis()
        Gets the time remaining for this execution in milliseconds

      • getMemoryLimitInMB

        int getMemoryLimitInMB()
        Gets the memory size configured for the Lambda function

      • getLogger

        LambdaLogger getLogger()
        Gets a the lambda logger instance associated with the context object
